On February 28, 2017, President Trump signed an executive order to recognize the importance of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). He emphasized the significance of education in uplifting and transforming lives, as well as promoting equality and justice. HBCUs have been pillars of the African-American community for over 150 years, and the executive order aims to prioritize their role in the White House. The President congratulated the individuals surrounding him for their work and thanked them on behalf of the country.